It’s official: TARA REID is the new cover of MR WARBURTON Magazine! From Y2K And Back Again, 40 Years Of Entertainment.  Tara sits down to talk about her 40 year career in the entertainment business & her love for her craft. But with fame comes sacrifice and Tara definitely has been through it all with the media. Plus, in a @pagesix exclusive she joins the ranks of #chelseahandler & #jenniferaniston on the pressures from #Hollywood  to get married and have a baby. It’s a must read!  Editors Note: I love Tara, she is a Y2K icon! I have known her for years now and is one of the kindest women I know. I’m so happy to honor her 40 year anniversary in the business with our cover! HUGE CONGRATULATIONS 🎈🎊🎉 to @tarareid on her new cover of @mr.warburtonmagazine & the fabulous cover launch party for the opening night of #pride sponsored by @vintagedistilling … we love to see our cover ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️shine throughout media! Thank you to @pagesix for working with us on the exclusive launch & all of the outlets who helped amplify our story and her voice!  Since the launch of #MRWARBURTONMAGAZINE we have brought you stories with meaning. We strive to give a voice to the misunderstood and  to the worlds most celebrated people, who are more likely than not equally misunderstood. Our mission is to allow artists to live in their truth and express their true selves. It’s not only our job but it’s our privilege. Thank you Tara for allowing us to enhance your life journey and playing with your already iconic image! You are an incredible ally to the community 💛❤️💚💜💙🧡 along with being an incredible person. We are so happy we got to have fun with you!

It’s official: actress Tara Reid is the new cover of the Los Angeles Inquisitor!
.
Straight off of the new @foxtv reality show ‘Special Forces: World’s Toughest Test’, actress and Y2K icon @tarareid sits down to talk to Los Angeles Inquisitor Editor-In-Chief @derekwarburton in this very personal interview. She goes in-depth on why she chose to do the physically challenging competition show and the demons she continues to fight inside of her. Plus, we addressed the bullies and their constant taunting of her body image. 
Tara has had enough. And sets the record straight on her alleged Bell’s palsy, anorexia and bulimia. With all of that said, a light came through the darkness. She became emotional after discovering that her fans came out in droves to support her. From Instagram DMs to tweets, Tara is feeling the love and couldn’t be more grateful. 
At 47 years old, Tara Raid is finding her strength. After years of living in darkness she has found love in her family, friends & her adoring fans. This is a must watch interview on loving yourself enough to be yourself.
.
.
.

In a Los Angeles Inquisitor video  exclusive: Actress Tara Reid sits down with editor in chief Derek Warburton respond  to online bullying and allegations of an eating disorder. She defends herself from all of the speculation and is grateful she has found her power to stand up against her internal fears. You don’t want to miss it. For the full interview, #linkinbio  Www.losangelesinquisitor.com

Wishing everyone love and light.
